        content: "Debate trains you to build and deliver arguments orally. Argumentative writing applies those same skills to the written word, and the transfer is remarkably natural once you understand the key differences.\n\nStrong argumentative writing is in demand everywhere: academic essays, opinion editorials, grant proposals, business cases, legal briefs, policy memos, and even persuasive emails. The ability to construct a clear, evidence-based written argument is a skill that will serve you throughout your education and career.\n\nIn this lesson, you will learn how to translate your debate structure, evidence analysis, and persuasive techniques into powerful written arguments. You will also practice editing a piece of writing to strengthen its argumentative structure.",
